{"type":"message","id":"f8c3a049","parentId":"f65ee881","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:21:42.971Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_60j2nhk1f3s1_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[32;1mName                                [0m[32;1m LastWriteTime[0m\r\n[32;1m----                                [0m [32;1m-------------[0m\r\n__pycache__                          3/22/2026 12:15:56 PM\r\nexperiment_11_moe_cache_sharing.py   3/22/2026 12:15:46 PM\r\nexperiment_7_shared_kv_pooling.py    3/22/2026 12:15:20 PM\r\ncompound_breakthrough_experiments.py 3/22/2026 12:13:03 PM\r\ninsight_discovery_analyzer.py        3/21/2026 1:53:27 PM\r\ntask_performance.py                  3/17/2026 7:14:29 PM\r\ntechnical_benchmark.py               3/17/2026 7:14:29 PM\r\nverify_results.py                    3/17/2026 7:14:29 PM\r\nrun_reasoning_experiments.py         3/17/2026 7:14:29 PM\r\nrun_breakthrough_discovery.py        3/17/2026 7:14:29 PM\r\nrun_all_experiments.py               3/17/2026 7:14:29 PM\r\nrun_all_experiments_v2.py            3/17/2026 7:14:29 PM\r\nrun_advanced_experiments.py          3/17/2026 7:14:29 PM\r\nresults                              3/17/2026 7:14:29 PM\r\nquality_analysis.py                  3/17/2026 7:14:29 PM"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":817,"aggregated":"[32;1mName                                [0m[32;1m LastWriteTime[0m\r\n[32;1m----                                [0m [32;1m-------------[0m\r\n__pycache__                          3/22/2026 12:15:56 PM\r\nexperiment_11_moe_cache_sharing.py   3/22/2026 12:15:46 PM\r\nexperiment_7_shared_kv_pooling.py    3/22/2026 12:15:20 PM\r\ncompound_breakthrough_experiments.py 3/22/2026 12:13:03 PM\r\ninsight_discovery_analyzer.py        3/21/2026 1:53:27 PM\r\ntask_performance.py                  3/17/2026 7:14:29 PM\r\ntechnical_benchmark.py               3/17/2026 7:14:29 PM\r\nverify_results.py                    3/17/2026 7:14:29 PM\r\nrun_reasoning_experiments.py         3/17/2026 7:14:29 PM\r\nrun_breakthrough_discovery.py        3/17/2026 7:14:29 PM\r\nrun_all_experiments.py               3/17/2026 7:14:29 PM\r\nrun_all_experiments_v2.py            3/17/2026 7:14:29 PM\r\nrun_advanced_experiments.py          3/17/2026 7:14:29 PM\r\nresults                              3/17/2026 7:14:29 PM\r\nquality_analysis.py                  3/17/2026 7:14:29 PM","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774354902921}}
{"type":"message","id":"91c40a6e","parentId":"f8c3a049","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:21:47.666Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see `experiment_11_moe_cache_sharing.py` and `experiment_7_shared_kv_pooling.py` - those are MoE-related experiments. So SR-MoE was being worked on within EXP. Let me look at the most recent experiment file and the results.","thinkingSignature":"d1973781e3263e705ba3081b3aab4cce44d942786fe743759c75bfadf1122d45"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5aq20muqyn2l_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\dev\\EXP\\experiments\\experiment_11_moe_cache_sharing.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5aq20muqyn2l_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem C:\\dev\\EXP\\results\\ | Select-Object Name, LastWriteTime | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First 10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5365,"output":155,"cacheRead":14175,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19695,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774354902972}}
{"type":"message","id":"b1071957","parentId":"91c40a6e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:21:48.191Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5aq20muqyn2l_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nExperiment 11: Cross-Model MoE Cache Sharing\r\n\r\nGoal:\r\n  Simulate MoE-style expert reuse across requests/models and measure memory\r\n  savings plus batch-size gains when KV blocks for shared experts are pooled.\r\n\r\nScenarios:\r\n  - Baseline: independent KV allocation per request/expert\r\n  - CAAE: shared expert KV blocks across requests/models\r\n\r\nMetrics:\r\n  - Total memory footprint (GB)\r\n  - Per-request memory (MB)\r\n  - Memory reduction (%)\r\n  - Simulated P99 latency (ms)\r\n  - Batch multiplier (for equal memory)\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport json\r\nimport statistics\r\nimport time\r\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import Dict, List, Tuple\r\n\r\nimport numpy as np\r\n\r\n\r\nBYTES_PER_TOKEN = 100.0\r\n\r\n\r\n@dataclass\r\nclass MoERequest:\r\n    request_id: str\r\n    model_id: str\r\n    experts_used: List[str]\r\n    tokens_per_expert: int\r\n    system_tokens: int = 4000\r\n    allocated_blocks: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)\r\n    total_memory_bytes: int = 0\r\n\r\n\r\ndef make_requests(\r\n    batch_size: int,\r\n    expert_pool: List[str],\r\n    experts_per_req: int,\r\n    tokens_per_expert: int,\r\n    system_tokens: int,\r\n    model_ids: List[str],\r\n    zipf_param: float = 1.1,\r\n) -> List[MoERequest]:\r\n    reqs: List[MoERequest] = []\r\n    for i in range(batch_size):\r\n        model_id = np.random.choice(model_ids)\r\n        experts = []\r\n        for _ in range(experts_per_req):\r\n            idx = int(np.random.zipf(zipf_param)) % len(expert_pool)\r\n            experts.append(expert_pool[idx])\r\n        experts = list(set(experts))\r\n        reqs.append(\r\n            MoERequest(\r\n                request_id=f\"req_{i:04d}\",\r\n                model_id=model_id,\r\n                experts_used=experts,\r\n                tokens_per_expert=tokens_per_expert,\r\n                system_tokens=system_tokens,\r\n            )\r\n        )\r\n    return reqs\r\n\r\n\r\ndef baseline_memory(reqs: List[MoERequest]) -> Dict:\r\n    total = 0\r\n    for r in reqs:\r\n        mem = r.system_tokens * BYTES_PER_TOKEN\r\n        for ex in r.experts_used:\r\n            mem += r.tokens_per_expert * BYTES_PER_TOKEN\r\n        total += mem\r\n    avg_per_req = total / len(reqs)\r\n    return {\r\n        \"total_bytes\": int(total),\r\n        \"total_gb\": total / (1024**3),\r\n        \"avg_per_request_mb\": avg_per_req / (1024**2),\r\n    }\r\n\r\n\r\ndef shared_memory(reqs: List[MoERequest]) -> Dict:\r\n    blocks: Dict[str, int] = {}\r\n    # system prompt shared globally\r\n    blocks[\"system_prompt\"] = int(reqs[0].system_tokens * BYTES_PER_TOKEN)\r\n    for r in reqs:\r\n        for ex in r.experts_used:\r\n            blocks.setdefault(ex, int(r.tokens_per_expert * BYTES_PER_TOKEN))\r\n    total = sum(blocks.values())\r\n    avg_per_req = total / len(reqs)\r\n    return {\r\n        \"total_bytes\": int(total),\r\n        \"total_gb\": total / (1024**3),\r\n        \"avg_per_request_mb\": avg_per_req / (1024**2),\r\n        \"num_shared_blocks\": len(blocks),\r\n    }\r\n\r\n\r\ndef simulate_latency(\r\n    total_gb: float,\r\n    batch: int,\r\n    is_shared: bool = False,\r\n    memory_reduction_percent: float = 0.0,\r\n    gpu_memory_gb: float = 80.0,\r\n    gpu_bandwidth_gb_s: float = 2e3,\r\n) -> float:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Memory-aware latency simulation (v2).\r\n\r\n    Replaces the old v1 model which used an absolute 50GB threshold —\r\n    meaningless for experiment regimes at 0.003–0.05GB.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    # Effective memory after pooling\r\n    effective_gb = total_gb * (1 - memory_reduction_percent / 100) if is_shared else total_gb\r\n\r\n    # Compute floor\r\n    compute_ms = 100.0\r\n\r\n    # Memory bandwidth cost (decode phase is memory-bound)\r\n    bandwidth_cost_ms = (effective_gb / gpu_bandwidth_gb_s) * 1000\r\n\r\n    # Batch penalty: scales with effective working set, reduced by pooling\r\n    batch_multiplier = batch * (1 - (memory_reduction_percent / 100) * 0.5)\r\n    batch_penalty_ms = batch_multiplier * 12.0\r\n\r\n    # L2 benefit: smaller working set = better cache hit rate\r\n    memory_fraction = effective_gb / gpu_memory_gb\r\n    l2_hit_rate = min(0.90, memory_fraction * 10)\r\n    l2_benefit_ms = (1 - l2_hit_rate) * bandwidth_cost_ms * 0.4\r\n\r\n    # Lookup overhead for shared pools (added cost)\r\n    lookup_overhead_ms = 2.0 if is_shared else 0.0\r\n\r\n    latency_ms = (\r\n        compute_ms\r\n        + bandwidth_cost_ms\r\n        + batch_penalty_ms\r\n        + lookup_overhead_ms\r\n        - l2_benefit_ms\r\n        + np.random.normal(0, 3)\r\n    )\r\n    return max(50, latency_ms)\r\n\r\n\r\ndef run_profile(profile_name: str, config: Dict) -> Dict:\r\n    batch_sizes = config[\"batch_sizes\"]\r\n    results = {\"baseline\": [], \"caae\": []}\r\n\r\n    for batch in batch_sizes:\r\n        reqs = make_requests(\r\n            batch_size=batch,\r\n            expert_pool=config[\"experts\"],\r\n            experts_per_req=config[\"experts_per_request\"],\r\n            tokens_per_expert=config[\"tokens_per_expert\"],\r\n            system_tokens=config[\"system_tokens\"],\r\n            model_ids=config[\"model_ids\"],\r\n            zipf_param=config.get(\"zipf_param\", 1.1),\r\n        )\r\n        base = baseline_memory(reqs)\r\n        shared = shared_memory(reqs)\r\n\r\n        reduction = ((base[\"total_gb\"] - shared[\"total_gb\"]) / base[\"total_gb\"]) * 100\r\n\r\n        base_lat = simulate_latency(base[\"total_gb\"], batch, is_shared=False)\r\n        shared_lat = simulate_latency(\r\n            shared[\"total_gb\"],\r\n            batch,\r\n            is_shared=True,\r\n            memory_reduction_percent=reduction,\r\n        )\r\n        lat_improvement = ((base_lat - shared_lat) / base_lat) * 100\r\n\r\n        base[\"batch_size\"] = batch\r\n        base[\"latency_ms\"] = base_lat\r\n        shared[\"batch_size\"] = batch\r\n        shared[\"latency_ms\"] = shared_lat\r\n        shared[\"reduction_percent\"] = reduction\r\n        shared[\"latency_improvement_percent\"] = lat_improvement\r\n\r\n        results[\"baseline\"].append(base)\r\n        results[\"caae\"].append(shared)\r\n\r\n    improvements = [r[\"reduction_percent\"] for r in results[\"caae\"]]\r\n    summary = {\r\n        \"avg_reduction_percent\": round(statistics.mean(improvements), 2),\r\n        \"max_reduction_percent\": round(max(improvements), 2),\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    return {\"profile\": profile_name, \"results\": results, \"summary\": summary}\r\n\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    np.random.seed(7)\r\n    timestamp = time.strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\")\r\n\r\n    configs = {\r\n        \"high_overlap\": {\r\n            \"batch_sizes\": [4, 8, 12, 16],\r\n            \"experts\": [f\"expert_{i}\" for i in range(4)],\r\n            \"experts_per_request\": 2,\r\n            \"tokens_per_expert\": 12000,\r\n            \"system_tokens\": 4000,\r\n            \"model_ids\": [\"mixtral-8x22b\", \"llama-70b\"],\r\n            \"zipf_param\": 1.05,\r\n        },\r\n        \"mixed_overlap\": {\r\n            \"batch_sizes\": [6, 12, 18, 24],\r\n            \"experts\": [f\"expert_{i}\" for i in range(12)],\r\n            \"experts_per_request\": 3,\r\n            \"tokens_per_expert\": 8000,\r\n            \"system_tokens\": 2500,\r\n            \"model_ids\": [\"mixtral-8x22b\", \"llama-70b\", \"gpt-4-turbo\"],\r\n            \"zipf_param\": 1.2,\r\n        },\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    profiles = []\r\n    for name, cfg in configs.items():\r\n        profiles.append(run_profile(name, cfg))\r\n\r\n    output = {\r\n        \"experiment\": \"11_moe_cache_sharing\",\r\n        \"timestamp\": timestamp,\r\n        \"profiles\": profiles,\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    out_path = Path(__file__).parent.parent / \"data\" / \"experiment_11_results.json\"\r\n    out_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\r\n    with open(out_path, \"w\") as f:\r\n        json.dump(output, f, indent=2)\r\n\r\n    print(\"=\" * 80)\r\n    print(\"EXPERIMENT 11: MoE Cache Sharing\")\r\n    print(\"=\" * 80)\r\n    for p in profiles:\r\n        print(f\"\\nProfile: {p['profile']}\")\r\n        print(f\"  Avg reduction: {p['summary']['avg_reduction_percent']:.1f}%\")\r\n        print(f\"  Max reduction: {p['summary']['max_reduction_percent']:.1f}%\")\r\n    print(f\"\\nResults saved to: {out_path}\")\r\n\r\n\r\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\r\n    main()\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774354908124}}
