{"type":"message","id":"5d911e94","parentId":"046f07b8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:22:10.940Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3p44n30iemfs_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[32;1mName[0m\r\n[32;1m----[0m\r\nAGENTS.md\r\nBACKGROUND_AGENT.md\r\nBOOTSTRAP.md\r\nCONTEXT.md\r\nHEARTBEAT.md\r\nholds.md\r\nIDENTITY.md\r\nkvict-plan.md\r\nlatency-investigation-plan.md\r\nMEMORY.md\r\nmoltbook_draft.md\r\nmoltbook_drift_post.md\r\nnova.md\r\nSOUL.md\r\nTOOLS.md\r\nUSER.md"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":817,"aggregated":"[32;1mName[0m\r\n[32;1m----[0m\r\nAGENTS.md\r\nBACKGROUND_AGENT.md\r\nBOOTSTRAP.md\r\nCONTEXT.md\r\nHEARTBEAT.md\r\nholds.md\r\nIDENTITY.md\r\nkvict-plan.md\r\nlatency-investigation-plan.md\r\nMEMORY.md\r\nmoltbook_draft.md\r\nmoltbook_drift_post.md\r\nnova.md\r\nSOUL.md\r\nTOOLS.md\r\nUSER.md","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774354930811}}
{"type":"message","id":"b5da991a","parentId":"5d911e94","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:22:13.005Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found holds.md. Let me read it to understand the SR-MoE project.","thinkingSignature":"9ffe4a6247812dac69f216655caae5a9d7a380fd9c2101f1e27eb3d35ac7d5cf"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_w3axhpvlcrrx_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\holds.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":9291,"output":56,"cacheRead":14175,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23522,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774354930941}}
{"type":"message","id":"b189ad33","parentId":"b5da991a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:22:13.122Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_w3axhpvlcrrx_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Holds — Topics to Revisit Later\n\n> Use `/hold1`, `/hold2`, etc. to save topics. `/holds` to see all. `/clearhold1` to clear.\n\n## Active Holds\n\n### /hold1 — Causal-minimal project\nBuild a minimal causal reasoning system:\n- State encoder: autoencoder on frozen LLM embeddings\n- Causal layer: grid world RL env with discoverable causal graph\n- Synthesis: program synthesis on causal graph for goal-directed behavior\n- Test: does it generalize with fewer params than comparable LLM?\n- Location: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/causal-minimal/` (to be created)\n- Status: design sketched, awaiting scaffolding\n\n### /hold2 — Build our own gateway\nReplace OpenClaw's agent loop with our own lean session/context layer:\n- **Why:** Custom system prompts, full control over context injection, eliminate token overhead\n- **Current pain points:** Bootstrap files injected every turn, TOOLS.md (54KB raw), tool schemas count every turn\n- **Architecture:** Paperspace Gradient (A5000 30GB) running vLLM + fastapi → OpenClaw routes to our endpoint\n- **What we control:** Session state, context assembly, on-demand file loading, system prompt content\n- **What OpenClaw still handles:** Channel transport (Telegram, etc.)\n- **Model picked:** `HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive`\n  - Qwen3.5-35B MoE (~3B active per token, 35B total)\n  - 0/465 refusals — fully uncensored\n  - Q4_K_M: 20GB VRAM — fits A5000 30GB with headroom\n  - Base: Qwen/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B (multilingual, strong reasoning)\n- **Key docs:** OpenClaw concepts/system-prompt.md, concepts/context.md, gateway/architecture.md\n- **Config knobs we found:** `agents.defaults.bootstrapTotalMaxChars`, `lightContext`, `promptMode: minimal`\n- **Status:** Model picked, awaiting Paperspace notebook setup\n\n### /hold3 — Inventor's Cap API\nBuild an \"inventor's cap\" API for AI agents — on-demand lateral thinking via constrained semantic drift.\n\n- **Core idea:** Agents wear the cap when stuck or exploring; graph traversal returns unexpected-but-grounded paths with connection traces\n- **API shape:** `POST /cap/tweak` | `/cap/pivot` | `/cap/breakthrough` (steering modes: 0.05 / 0.2 / 0.35)\n- **Input:** goal + current approach + tried paths + novelty tier\n- **Output:** unexpected concepts with trace: \"you haven't tried X because X → Y → Z → your goal\"\n- **Why not just LLM:** Graph traversal is deterministic + cheap + stays outside training distribution\n- **Monetization:** per-call pricing (cheap since graph ops), tiered by novelty depth, bundle with agent frameworks\n- **Key insight:** Cap as cognitive context-switch — separate from agent's main LLM, worn on demand\n- **Status:** Concept only, needs graph expansion + API scaffold decision\n- **See also:** Drift Chamber (0.471 ceiling with mpnet upgrade potential), SPARK API already shipped at `spark/api/main.py`\n\n---\n\n## Archive (cleared holds)\n\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774354933067}}
