{"type":"message","id":"4d162dda","parentId":"b64fa5a8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:46:32.193Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. So:\n- Cell 2 (my new cell): Has FracturedSRMoEHead class + `SRMoEHead = FracturedSRMoEHead` alias\n- Cell 3 (Constants): Has RingAttractor, DiversityRegularizer, and OLD `class SRMoEHead` (monolithic)\n\nWhen the notebook runs:\n1. Cell 1: imports\n2. Cell 2: defines FracturedSRMoEHead and aliases SRMoEHead to it\n3. Cell 3: **redefines** `class SRMoEHead` as the OLD monolithic class! This overwrites the alias.\n\n\n4. Cell 4 (ArchitectureB): uses `SRMoEHead` - gets the OLD class\n\nSo I need to delete the old SRMoEHead class from cell 3 but keep RingAttractor and DiversityRegularizer. The cleanest approach is to just remove the old SRMoEHead and diversity_loss method from cell 3, leaving the other two classes intact.\n\nCell 3 currently has all three classes together: RingAttractor (lines 6-53), DiversityRegularizer (lines 54-82), and SRMoEHead (lines 83-154). I'll write a script to surgically remove lines 83-154 from cell 3's source.","thinkingSignature":"c46669d7cfb8ed26d32a5f2bd6899ebd5f0845326bf5c49b31119fa4352eec2c"},{"type":"text","text":"Cell 3 redefines the old `class SRMoEHead` after my alias — it would overwrite it. I need to remove the old SRMoEHead class from cell 3 (keeping RingAttractor and DiversityRegularizer):\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uejh9y2yyvw5_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\fix_srmoe.py","content":"import json\n\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    nb = json.load(f)\n\n# Cell 3 has the old SRMoEHead class. We need to remove it.\n# Keep RingAttractor (lines 6-53) and DiversityRegularizer (lines 54-82).\n# Remove the SRMoEHead class (lines 83 onwards) from that cell.\n\ncell3 = nb['cells'][3]\nlines = cell3['source']\n\n# Find the start of SRMoEHead class and the end of the file\nsrmoe_start = None\nfor i, line in enumerate(lines):\n    if 'class SRMoEHead' in line:\n        srmoe_start = i\n        break\n\nprint(f\"SRMoEHead class starts at line {srmoe_start}\")\nprint(f\"Total lines in cell 3: {len(lines)}\")\nprint(f\"Lines to remove: {srmoe_start} to {len(lines)-1} ({len(lines)-srmoe_start} lines)\")\n\n# Keep lines 0 to srmoe_start - 1 (everything before SRMoEHead)\n# Add a comment to indicate the class was moved\nkept_lines = lines[:srmoe_start]\nkept_lines.append(\"\\n# SRMoEHead moved to FracturedSRMoEHead (see cell 2)\\n\")\n\ncell3['source'] = kept_lines\nprint(f\"Cell 3 now has {len(kept_lines)} lines\")\n\n# Verify: cell 3 should NOT have 'class SRMoEHead'\nsrc3 = ''.join(cell3['source'])\nassert 'class SRMoEHead' not in src3, \"ERROR: old SRMoEHead still in cell 3!\"\nassert 'class RingAttractor' in src3, \"ERROR: RingAttractor removed from cell 3!\"\nassert 'class DiversityRegularizer' in src3, \"ERROR: DiversityRegularizer removed from cell 3!\"\nprint(\"Verification passed: cell 3 has RingAttractor + DiversityRegularizer, no SRMoEHead\")\n\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    json.dump(nb, f, ensure_ascii=False)\n\nprint(\"Notebook saved.\")\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":85672,"output":867,"cacheRead":14175,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":100714,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774356372283}}
