{"type":"message","id":"b8f59373","parentId":"bea382a0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:51:29.545Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error is clear: `torch.stack([shard_h, shard_b, shard_r, shard_c])` fails because they have different sizes:\n- shard_h: [32]\n- shard_b: [16]\n- shard_r: [16]\n- shard_c: [24]\n\nWhen you torch.stack vectors of different sizes, it fails. I need to either:\n1. Make them all the same size (pad smaller ones to match the largest)\n2. Just not use torch.stack for the confidence bias — instead compute the weighted sum differently\n\nOption 2 is cleaner: since vote_probs is [4] and the shards have different sizes, I can't just matmul directly. \n\nI'll compute the confidence bias by manually applying each shard's weight to its corresponding embedding and summing them together, since the varying tensor sizes prevent a straightforward stack and matmul approach.","thinkingSignature":"0b86f2fb8e99b8a6150acdd0a8e8e936ce3bc3480da0c10142284ae453469a04"},{"type":"text","text":"Quick fix — the shards have different sizes so `torch.stack` fails. The confidence bias just needs to sum weighted shards element-wise instead of trying to matmul them:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_io1o0avcadg3_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\fix_stack.py","content":"import json\n\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    nb = json.load(f)\n\ncell2_src = ''.join(nb['cells'][2]['source'])\n\n# Find and replace the buggy torch.stack confidence bias\nold = \"        shards = torch.stack([shard_h, shard_b, shard_r, shard_c])\\n        confidence_bias = vote_confidence.detach() * (vote_probs @ shards)\"\nnew = \"        # Weighted sum: vote_probs[i] * shard[i], then scale by confidence\\n        # (can't torch.stack — shards have different sizes: 32, 16, 16, 24)\\n        confidence_bias = vote_confidence.detach() * (\\n            vote_probs[0] * shard_h +\\n            vote_probs[1] * shard_b +\\n            vote_probs[2] * shard_r +\\n            vote_probs[3] * shard_c\\n        )\"\n\nif old in cell2_src:\n    new_src = cell2_src.replace(old, new)\n    nb['cells'][2]['source'] = [new_src]\n    with open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n        json.dump(nb, f, ensure_ascii=False)\n    print(\"Fixed: replaced torch.stack bias with element-wise weighted sum\")\n    print(\"Old lines matched and replaced.\")\nelse:\n    print(\"ERROR: could not find the exact old text to replace\")\n    print(\"Searching for 'torch.stack' in cell 2:\")\n    for i, line in enumerate(new_src.split('\\n')):\n        if 'torch.stack' in line or 'shards' in line:\n            print(f\"  line {i}: {repr(line)}\")\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":642,"cacheRead":14175,"cacheWrite":76138,"totalTokens":90998,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774356669990}}
