{"type":"message","id":"2eb1b792","parentId":"694255a8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:55:50.527Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that when doing `vote_probs[0] * shard_h + vote_probs[1] * shard_b + ...`, the broadcasting is wrong. `vote_probs[0]` is a scalar tensor, `shard_h` is [32]. Then `vote_probs[1] * shard_b` where `shard_b` is [16]. When we try to add [32] + [16], it fails.\n\nI need to zero-pad the smaller shard embeddings to the same size (32) before summing. Let me fix this properly.","thinkingSignature":"212160e132019cc88e166376b014232744932898c48459c8781bb4fe098bc167"},{"type":"text","text":"Broadcasting mismatch — `[32] + [16]` fails when adding them together. Need to zero-pad smaller shards up to the max size (32) before summing:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_om8hsd53k4v2_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\fix_stack.py","content":"import json\n\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    nb = json.load(f)\n\ncell2_src = ''.join(nb['cells'][2]['source'])\n\n# Replace the broken element-wise sum with proper zero-padded weighted sum\nold = \"        # Small confidence-weighted bias (detach so conf doesn't cheat)\\n        # Weighted sum: vote_probs[i] * shard[i], then scale by confidence\\n        # (can't torch.stack — shards have different sizes: 32, 16, 16, 24)\\n        confidence_bias = vote_confidence.detach() * (\\n            vote_probs[0] * shard_h +\\n            vote_probs[1] * shard_b +\\n            vote_probs[2] * shard_r +\\n            vote_probs[3] * shard_c\\n        )\"\n\nnew = \"        # Confidence-weighted bias: weighted sum of shard embeddings, zero-padded\\n        # to the largest shard size (32). vote_probs[i] is a scalar weight per shard.\\n        # vote_confidence modulates the overall strength of the bias.\\n        max_shard_dim = 32  # shard_hidden is always the largest at 32\\n        bias = torch.zeros(max_shard_dim, device=device)\\n        bias[:shard_h.shape[0]] += vote_probs[0] * shard_h\\n        bias[:shard_b.shape[0]] += vote_probs[1] * shard_b\\n        bias[:shard_r.shape[0]] += vote_probs[2] * shard_r\\n        bias[:shard_c.shape[0]] += vote_probs[3] * shard_c\\n        confidence_bias = vote_confidence.detach() * bias\"\n\nif old in cell2_src:\n    new_src = cell2_src.replace(old, new)\n    nb['cells'][2]['source'] = [new_src]\n    with open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n        json.dump(nb, f, ensure_ascii=False)\n    print(\"Fixed: zero-padded weighted sum for confidence bias\")\nelse:\n    print(\"ERROR: could not find the old text\")\n    # Show what's actually there around line 119\n    lines = cell2_src.split('\\n')\n    for i in range(114, 130):\n        if i < len(lines):\n            print(f\"  {i}: {repr(lines[i])}\")\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":725,"cacheRead":90001,"cacheWrite":2907,"totalTokens":93676,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774356928860}}
