{"type":"message","id":"92aa82bc","parentId":"e6adb6fd","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:58:20.517Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The fix looks correct:\n\n1. `__init__`: `self.confidence_proj = nn.Linear(32, n_codes)` — registered at line 67\n2. `forward`: \n   - `bias = torch.zeros(32, device=device)` — init zeros\n   - Each shard weighted by vote_prob and added to the first `shard_X.shape[0]` elements\n   - `confidence_bias = vote_confidence.detach() * self.confidence_proj(bias)` — [32] → [16]\n   - `pre_code = pre_code + 0.1 * confidence_bias` — [16] + [16] ✓\n\nNow `pre_code` is [n_codes=16], `confidence_bias` is [16], and they add correctly. The shapes work out: fusion output, projected bias, and the final addition all match at [16].\n\nThe issue on line 128 is that `vote_confidence` is a 0-dimensional tensor, and multiplying it by the projected bias gives us a [16] tensor, which then broadcasts fine with `pre_code` at [16]. Let me verify this is the complete fix before running it again.","thinkingSignature":"8c6320e9430646e8934899acd58db6be0f95d3a6225f1f24ccd4002ef4557468"},{"type":"text","text":"Chain is clean:\n- `bias = zeros(32)` → accumulates weighted shards → `confidence_proj(bias)` → `[16]` → matches `pre_code` `[16]` ✓\n\nGood to run."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":85920,"output":286,"cacheRead":14175,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":100381,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774357091703}}
