{"type":"message","id":"539f793b","parentId":"46226a76","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:34:35.242Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is asking two things:\n1. Implement DAgger in the notebook\n2. A personal question about whether this work will lead to success/notoriety\n\nLet me address both honestly. First, let me implement DAgger. Then give a real answer to the personal question.\n\nFor the implementation, I need to:\n1. Add `get_oracle_action` helper to ArchitectureB\n2. Add `DAggerReplayBuffer` class\n3. Modify `SRMoETrainer` to support DAgger collection\n4. Add `run_dagger_collection_episode` \n5. Modify Phase 2 loop with beta schedule\n\n\n6. Assess the trajectory honestly\n\nOn the likelihood of success — the core technical problems are genuinely hard. Phase 2 collapse keeps recurring even after architectural fixes like the fractured head, which suggests the distributional shift between oracle and learned routing is the real bottleneck rather than just a capacity issue. DAgger addresses this at a principled level, but it's not a silver bullet. That said, even partial success on an associative memory task with bounded compute is publishable and noteworthy.\n\nThe honest reality is that notoriety and a successful research career require more than just good ideas — timing, visibility, networking, and marketing matter enormously. A solid paper at NeurIPS or ICML is achievable, but \"getting a life\" in the way I think Zach means it — financial independence, creative freedom, recognition — that depends on factors far beyond this single project. I should be direct about this rather than offering false reassurance.","thinkingSignature":"73e332951d48213ad5bdd746a3176903ae076bf2a38c1a375c25d62b96af867f"},{"type":"text","text":"On the DAgger implementation — doing it now. On the personal question — let me be real with you after.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_12vxlkiloug2_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\implement_dagger.py","content":"import json, sys\n\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    nb = json.load(f)\n\n# ── Helper: find cell index by content marker ────────────────────────────────\ndef find_cell(keyword):\n    for i, cell in enumerate(nb['cells']):\n        src = ''.join(cell.get('source', []))\n        if keyword in src:\n            return i\n    return None\n\narchB_idx = find_cell('class ArchitectureB')\ntrainer_idx = find_cell('class SRMoETrainer')\ntraining_idx = find_cell('Phase 2')\nprint(f\"ArchitectureB: cell {archB_idx}, SRMoETrainer: cell {trainer_idx}, Training: cell {training_idx}\")\n\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# CELL A: DAgger infrastructure (insert after fractured head cell, index 2)\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\ncell_dagger = {\n    \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n    \"execution_count\": None,\n    \"id\": \"dagger-infra\",\n    \"metadata\": {},\n    \"outputs\": [],\n    \"source\": [\n        \"# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\\n\",\n        \"# DAgger: Dataset Aggregation for Phase 2\\n\",\n        \"#\\n\",\n        \"# Problem: Phase 1 trains router on oracle-routed episodes (optimal memory,\\n\",\n        \"# optimal budget). Phase 2 runs the learned policy, which visits DIFFERENT\\n\",\n        \"# states — different memory content, different budget levels. The oracle\\n\",\n        \"# never saw those states. Classic distributional shift.\\n\",\n        \"#\\n\",\n        \"# DAgger fix: run the current policy, query the oracle at each step,\\n\",\n        \"# collect (state, oracle_action) pairs. Train on both DAgger data AND\\n\",\n        \"# fresh oracle episodes. The training distribution now matches inference.\\n\",\n        \"#\\n\",\n        \"# Safety: episodes with blocked_frac > 0.6 are discarded — the policy\\n\",\n        \"# routed so badly the episode is unrecoverable. Training on those states\\n\",\n        \"# would accelerate collapse, not fix it.\\n\",\n        \"# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"class DAggerReplayBuffer:\\n\",\n        \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n        \"    FIFO replay buffer for DAgger (state, oracle_action) transitions.\\n\",\n        \"    State = (hidden, budget_norm, step_pos, step_parity, is_query_phase)\\n\",\n        \"    Only stores tensors that are safe to clone (hidden is 1D). Ring state\\n\",\n        \"    is NOT stored — it is deterministically reconstructable from hidden\\n\",\n        \"    via the ring attractor's input projection, so recomputing it is free.\\n\",\n        \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n        \"    def __init__(self, max_size=5000):\\n\",\n        \"        self.max_size = max_size\\n\",\n        \"        self.buffer = []\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"    def append(self, hidden, budget_norm, step_pos, step_parity, is_query, oracle_action_idx):\\n\",\n        \"        entry = {\\n\",\n        \"            'hidden': hidden.detach().clone(),\\n\",\n        \"            'budget_norm': budget_norm,\\n\",\n        \"            'step_pos': step_pos,\\n\",\n        \"            'step_parity': step_parity,\\n\",\n        \"            'is_query': is_query,\\n\",\n        \"            'oracle_action': oracle_action_idx,\\n\",\n        \"        }\\n\",\n        \"        self.buffer.append(entry)\\n\",\n        \"        if len(self.buffer) > self.max_size:\\n\",\n        \"            self.buffer.pop(0)\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"    def sample(self, batch_size, device):\\n\",\n        \"        if len(self.buffer) == 0:\\n\",\n        \"            return None\\n\",\n        \"        indices = random.sample(range(len(self.buffer)), min(batch_size, len(self.buffer)))\\n\",\n        \"        hiddens     = torch.stack([self.buffer[i]['hidden'] for i in indices])\\n\",\n        \"        budget_norms= torch.tensor([self.buffer[i]['budget_norm'] for i in indices], dtype=torch.float, device=device)\\n\",\n        \"        step_pos    = torch.tensor([self.buffer[i]['step_pos'] for i in indices], dtype=torch.float, device=device)\\n\",\n        \"        step_parity = torch.tensor([self.buffer[i]['step_parity'] for i in indices], dtype=torch.float, device=device)\\n\",\n        \"        is_query    = torch.tensor([self.buffer[i]['is_query'] for i in indices], dtype=torch.float, device=device)\\n\",\n        \"        oracle_acts = torch.tensor([self.buffer[i]['oracle_action'] for i in indices], dtype=torch.long, device=device)\\n\",\n        \"        return hiddens, budget_norms, step_pos, step_parity, is_query, oracle_acts\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"    def __len__(self): return len(self.buffer)\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"def dagger_collection_episode(model, episode, buffer, device, max_blocked_frac=0.6):\\n\",\n        \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n        \"    Run one episode with the CURRENT (partially learned) policy, collect\\n\",\n        \"    (state, oracle_action) pairs for DAgger.\\n\",\n        \"    \\n\",\n        \"    This does NOT modify model state permanently — ring state is saved/restored\\n\",\n        \"    around each oracle query so the trajectory is unaffected by the oracle call.\\n\",\n        \"    \\n\",\n        \"    Returns: dict of metrics, or None if episode is too corrupted (blocked > threshold).\\n\",\n        \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n        \"    m = model.eval()\\n\",\n        \"    m.reset_episode()\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"    # Temporary storage for this episode's transitions\\n\",\n        \"    episode_hidden = []\\n\",\n        \"    episode_budget = []\\n\",\n        \"    episode_step_pos = []\\n\",\n        \"    episode_step_parity = []\\n\",\n        \"    episode_is_query = []\\n\",\n        \"    episode_oracle_act = []\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"    skip_cnt = read_cnt = write_cnt = blocked_cnt = 0\\n\",\n        \"    encode_occupancies = []\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"    with torch.no_grad():\\n\",\n        \"        for t in range(len(episode.input_ids)):\\n\",\n        \"            tok = episode.input_ids[t].to(device)\\n\",\n        \"            is_query_step = (t >= QUERY_START)\\n\",\n        \"            budget_norm = m.budget.budget_remaining_normalised\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"            # ── Current policy forward pass ──────────────────────────────\\n\",\n        \"            logits, info = m(tok)\\n\",\n        \"            ai = info['action_idx']\\n\",\n        \"            \\n\",\n        \"            if ai == 0: skip_cnt += 1\\n\",\n        \"            elif ai == 1: read_cnt += 1\\n\",\n        \"            elif ai == 2: write_cnt += 1\\n\",\n        \"            if info.get('blocked'): blocked_cnt += 1\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"            if t < QUERY_START:\\n\",\n        \"                encode_occupancies.append(info['occupancy'])\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"            # ── Oracle query (no side effects) ─────────────────────────\\n\",\n        \"            # Save ring state before oracle call, restore after\\n\",\n        \"            saved_ring_state = m.routing.ring._ring_state.clone() if m.routing.ring._ring_state is not None else None\\n\",\n        \"            oracle_act_idx = _O2I.get(episode.oracle_actions[t], 0)\\n\",\n        \"            # Restore ring state — oracle query has zero side effects on trajectory\\n\",\n        \"            if saved_ring_state is not None:\\n\",\n        \"                m.routing.ring._ring_state = saved_ring_state\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"            # ── Collect transition ──────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n        \"            # Clone hidden to break graph (no gradient needed for DAgger collection)\\n\",\n        \"            episode_hidden.append(m._hidden.detach().clone())\\n\",\n        \"            episode_budget.append(budget_norm)\\n\",\n        \"            episode_step_pos.append(t / EPISODE_LENGTH)\\n\",\n        \"            episode_step_parity.append(float(t % 2))\\n\",\n        \"            episode_is_query.append(float(is_query_step))\\n\",\n        \"            episode_oracle_act.append(oracle_act_idx)\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"    n_steps = len(episode.input_ids)\\n\",\n        \"    blocked_frac = blocked_cnt / max(n_steps, 1)\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"    # Safety valve: discard episodes that are too corrupted\\n\",\n        \"    if blocked_frac > max_blocked_frac:\\n\",\n        \"        return None  # caller should skip adding to buffer\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"    # ── Add episode transitions to buffer ─────────────────────────────\\n\",\n        \"    for i in range(len(episode_hidden)):\\n\",\n        \"        buffer.append(\\n\",\n        \"            episode_hidden[i],\\n\",\n        \"            episode_budget[i],\\n\",\n        \"            episode_step_pos[i],\\n\",\n        \"            episode_step_parity[i],\\n\",\n        \"            episode_is_query[i],\\n\",\n        \"            episode_oracle_act[i]\\n\",\n        \"        )\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"    return {\\n\",\n        \"        'blocked_frac': blocked_frac,\\n\",\n        \"        'skip_frac': skip_cnt / n_steps,\\n\",\n        \"        'read_frac': read_cnt / n_steps,\\n\",\n        \"        'write_frac': write_cnt / n_steps,\\n\",\n        \"        'avg_occupancy': sum(encode_occupancies) / max(len(encode_occupancies), 1),\\n\",\n        \"        'buffer_size': len(buffer),\\n\",\n        \"    }\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"def dagger_loss_from_buffer(model, buffer, batch_size, device):\\n\",\n        \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n        \"    Compute DAgger loss from the replay buffer.\\n\",\n        \"    Samples batch_size transitions, runs them through the router (with gradient),\\n\",\n        \"    and computes CE against the oracle actions stored in the buffer.\\n\",\n        \"    \\n\",\n        \"    This trains the router on states visited by the CURRENT policy but with\\n\",\n        \"    oracle labels — bridging the distribution gap between oracle and learned routing.\\n\",\n        \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n        \"    batch = buffer.sample(batch_size, device)\\n\",\n        \"    if batch is None:\\n\",\n        \"        return torch.tensor(0.0, device=device), {}\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"    hiddens, budget_norms, step_pos, step_parity, is_query, oracle_acts = batch\\n\",\n        \"    \\n\",\n        \"    total_loss = torch.tensor(0.0, device=device)\\n\",\n        \"    n = hiddens.shape[0]\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"    # Route stop_grad = False — we WANT gradients here (this IS the training)\\n\",\n        \"    for i in range(n):\\n\",\n        \"        h = hiddens[i]  # [hidden_dim]\\n\",\n        \"        bn = budget_norms[i].item()\\n\",\n        \"        sp = step_pos[i].item()\\n\",\n        \"        sq = step_parity[i].item()\\n\",\n        \"        iq = is_query[i].item()\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"        # Forward through router — gradient flows back to router params\\n\",\n        \"        # We temporarily set the ring state from hidden (deterministic, no side effects)\\n\",\n        \"        m = model\\n\",\n        \"        saved_ring = m.routing.ring._ring_state.clone() if m.routing.ring._ring_state is not None else None\\n\",\n        \"        m.routing.ring._ring_state = None  # force ring to recompute from hidden\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"        router_logits, action_idx, salience = m.routing(\\n\",\n        \"            h, bn, sp, sq, iq\\n\",\n        \"        )\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"        # Restore ring state\\n\",\n        \"        m.routing.ring._ring_state = saved_ring\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"        oracle_action = oracle_acts[i]\\n\",\n        \"        if oracle_action.item() != IGNORE_INDEX:\\n\",\n        \"            step_loss = F.cross_entropy(\\n\",\n        \"                router_logits.unsqueeze(0),\\n\",\n        \"                oracle_action.unsqueeze(0)\\n\",\n        \"            )\\n\",\n        \"            total_loss = total_loss + step_loss\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"    avg_loss = total_loss / max(n, 1)\\n\",\n        \"    return avg_loss, {'dagger_n_samples': n}\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"print('DAgger infrastructure loaded')\\n\",\n    ]\n}\n\n# Insert after cell 2 (fractured head cell)\nnb['cells'].insert(3, cell_dagger)\nprint(f\"Inserted DAgger cell at position 3 (0-based)\")\n\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# CELL B: Modify SRMoETrainer to add DAgger method\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# We need to add a dagger_train_episode method to SRMoETrainer.\n# The trainer already exists — we'll insert a new cell AFTER the trainer cell\n# that monkey-patches the method onto the class.\n\ntrainer_patch = {\n    \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n    \"execution_count\": None,\n    \"id\": \"dagger-trainer-patch\",\n    \"metadata\": {},\n    \"outputs\": [],\n    \"source\": [\n        \"# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\\n\",\n        \"# DAgger training mixin: adds dagger_train_episode to SRMoETrainer\\n\",\n        \"#\\n\",\n        \"# Phase 2 now alternates between:\\n\",\n        \"#   1. DAgger collection: run current policy, populate replay buffer\\n\",\n        \"#   2. DAgger training: train on buffer samples + fresh oracle episodes\\n\",\n        \"#\\n\",\n        \"# beta schedule: start at 0.8 (mostly oracle), decay to 0.2 over DECAY_EPS\\n\",\n        \"# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"DAggerBuffer = DAggerReplayBuffer(max_size=5000)\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"DECAY_EPS = 500       # episodes over which beta decays from 0.8 to 0.2\\n\",\n        \"INIT_BETA = 0.8       # start: 80% oracle actions, 20% policy states\\n\",\n        \"FINAL_BETA = 0.2      # end: 20% oracle actions, 80% policy states\\n\",\n        \"DAGGER_COLLECT_EVERY = 3   # collect DAgger every N training steps\\n\",\n        \"DAGGER_BATCH_SIZE = 64     # DAgger samples per training step\\n\",\n        \"ORACLE_EPISODES_PER_STEP = 1  # fresh oracle episodes per step\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"def _beta_schedule(ep_in_phase2):\\n\",\n        \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"Linear decay from INIT_BETA to FINAL_BETA over DECAY_EPS.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n        \"    frac = min(ep_in_phase2 / max(DECAY_EPS - 1, 1), 1.0)\\n\",\n        \"    return INIT_BETA + frac * (FINAL_BETA - INIT_BETA)\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"def dagger_train_step(trainer, dagger_buffer, beta, device, collect_stats=None):\\n\",\n        \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n        \"    One DAgger training step:\\n\",\n        \"      - Sample DAGGER_BATCH_SIZE transitions from buffer, compute dagger loss\\n\",\n        \"      - Generate ORACLE_EPISODES_PER_STEP fresh oracle episodes, train on them\\n\",\n        \"      - Mix: dagger_loss * (1-beta) + oracle_loss * beta\\n\",\n        \"    \\n\",\n        \"    The dagger_loss is pre-collected (no forward pass here), so this step\\n\",\n        \"    only adds one forward pass for the oracle episodes.\\n\",\n        \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n        \"    # DAgger loss from buffer (already collected — no model forward needed here)\\n\",\n        \"    L_dagger, d_info = dagger_loss_from_buffer(\\n\",\n        \"        trainer.model, dagger_buffer, DAGGER_BATCH_SIZE, device\\n\",\n        \"    )\\n\",\n        \"    \\n\",\n        \"    # Fresh oracle episodes (baseline — same as original Phase 1 training)\\n\",\n        \"    L_oracle_total = torch.tensor(0.0, device=device)\\n\",\n        \"    oracle_stats = {}\\n\",\n        \"    for _ in range(ORACLE_EPISODES_PER_STEP):\\n\",\n        \"        ep_stats = trainer.train_episode(generate_episode(int(random.random() * 1e6)),\\n\",\n        \"                                       use_oracle_routing=True)\\n\",\n        \"        L_oracle_total = L_oracle_total + torch.tensor(ep_stats['loss'], device=device)\\n\",\n        \"        oracle_stats = ep_stats\\n\",\n        \"    L_oracle = L_oracle_total / ORACLE_EPISODES_PER_STEP\\n\",\n        \"    \\n\",\n        \"    # Mix: dagger_loss with weight (1-beta), oracle_loss with weight beta\\n\",\n        \"    # beta high = trust oracle more; beta low = trust policy more\\n\",\n        \"    L_mixed = (1 - beta) * L_dagger + beta * L_oracle\\n\",\n        \"    \\n\",\n        \"    trainer.opt.zero_grad()\\n\",\n        \"    L_mixed.backward()\\n\",\n        \"    torch.nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(trainer.params, 1.0)\\n\",\n        \"    trainer.opt.step()\\n\",\n        \"    \\n\",\n        \"    if collect_stats is not None:\\n\",\n        \"        collect_stats['dagger_loss'] = L_dagger.item()\\n\",\n        \"        collect_stats['oracle_loss'] = L_oracle.item()\\n\",\n        \"        collect_stats['mixed_loss'] = L_mixed.item()\\n\",\n        \"        collect_stats['beta'] = beta\\n\",\n        \"        collect_stats['buffer_size'] = len(dagger_buffer)\\n\",\n        \"        collect_stats['dagger_samples'] = d_info.get('dagger_n_samples', 0)\\n\",\n        \"        if oracle_stats:\\n\",\n        \"            collect_stats['oracle_acc'] = oracle_stats.get('accuracy', 0)\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"\\n\",\n        \"print('DAgger training mixin loaded')\\n\",\n        \"print(f'  beta schedule: {INIT_BETA} -> {FINAL_BETA} over {DECAY_EPS} eps')\\n\",\n        \"print(f'  DAgger collection every {DAGGER_COLLECT_EVERY} steps, batch_size={DAGGER_BATCH_SIZE}')\\n\",\n    ]\n}\n\n# Insert after trainer cell\nnb['cells'].insert(trainer_idx + 1, trainer_patch)\nprint(f\"Inserted DAgger trainer patch after cell {trainer_idx}\")\n\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# CELL C: Replace Phase 2 loop with DAgger version\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Find the training cell and replace its Phase 2 section\n\ntraining_cell_idx = training_idx\ntraining_src = ''.join(nb['cells'][training_cell_idx]['source'])\n\n# We need to replace the Phase 2 loop. Let's find the boundaries.\n# Phase 2 starts after \"### Phase 2: Learned Routing\" markdown.\nlines = nb['cells'][training_cell_idx]['source']\nphase2_start = None\nphase2_end = None\nfor i, line in enumerate(lines):\n    if '### Phase 2' in line:\n        phase2_start = i\n    if phase2_start is not None and '### Phase 3' in line:\n        phase2_end = i\n        break\n\nprint(f\"Phase 2 loop: lines {phase2_start} to {phase2_end}\")\n\n# Replace Phase 2 loop with DAgger version\nnew_phase2_lines = [\n    \"### Phase 2: Learned Routing (DAgger)\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"# DAgger: alternate between collecting trajectories and training on mixed batches.\\n\",\n    \"# Beta schedule: starts at 0.8 (mostly oracle), decays to 0.2 over 500 eps.\\n\",\n    \"# Buffer is shared across all Phase 2 — accumulates diverse policy states.\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"dagger_buffer = DAggerReplayBuffer(max_size=5000)\\n\",\n    \"phase2_ep = 0\\n\",\n    \"collect_every = 3  # collect DAgger every 3 training steps\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"for ep in range(PHASE2_EP):\\n\",\n    \"    phase2_ep += 1\\n\",\n    \"    beta = _beta_schedule(phase2_ep)\\n\",\n    \"    \\n\",\n    \"    # ── Every N steps: collect DAgger trajectory ──────────────────────\\n\",\n    \"    if phase2_ep % collect_every == 0:\\n\",\n    \"        coll_ep = generate_episode(DEEPSEED + ep + 100000)\\n\",\n    \"        coll_stats = dagger_collection_episode(model, coll_ep, dagger_buffer, DEVICE)\\n\",\n    \"        if coll_stats is None:\\n\",\n    \"            pass  # episode too corrupted — skip silently\\n\",\n    \"        elif phase2_ep % 200 == 0:\\n\",\n    \"            print(f'  dagger coll ep {phase2_ep}: blkd={coll_stats[\\\"blocked_frac\\\"]:.2f} '\\n\",\n    \"                  f'buf={coll_stats[\\\"buffer_size\\\"]} '\\n\",\n    \"                  f'wr={coll_stats[\\\"write_frac\\\"]:.2f} rd={coll_stats[\\\"read_frac\\\"]:.2f}')\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"    # ── Training step: mix DAgger buffer + fresh oracle episodes ───────\\n\",\n    \"    stats = {}\\n\",\n    \"    dagger_train_step(trainer, dagger_buffer, beta, DEVICE, collect_stats=stats)\\n\",\n    \"    \\n\",\n    \"    if phase2_ep % 200 == 0:\\n\",\n    \"        print(f'  p2 {phase2_ep:5d}: beta={beta:.2f} loss={stats.get(\\\"mixed_loss\\\",0):.4f} '\\n\",\n    \"              f'd_l={stats.get(\\\"dagger_loss\\\",0):.4f} o_l={stats.get(\\\"oracle_loss\\\",0):.4f} '\\n\",\n    \"              f'buf={stats.get(\\\"buffer_size\\\",0)} acc={stats.get(\\\"oracle_acc\\\",0):.3f}')\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n]\n\n# Replace lines phase2_start to phase2_end with new content\nnew_training_lines = lines[:phase2_start] + new_phase2_lines + lines[phase2_end:]\n\nnb['cells'][training_cell_idx]['source'] = new_training_lines\nprint(f\"Replaced Phase 2 loop (old lines {phase2_start}-{phase2_end}) with DAgger version\")\n\n# Save\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    json.dump(nb, f, ensure_ascii=False)\n\nprint(\"\\nNotebook saved — DAgger implementation complete.\")\nprint(\"\\nSummary of changes:\")\nprint(\"  Cell A (new, pos 3): DAggerReplayBuffer + dagger_collection_episode + dagger_loss_from_buffer\")\nprint(\"  Cell B (new, after trainer): dagger_train_step + beta schedule + DAggerBuffer init\")\nprint(\"  Cell C (modified training cell): Phase 2 loop replaced with DAgger alternating collection+training\")\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":5798,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":62572,"totalTokens":72659,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774359141638}}
