{"type":"message","id":"35c089fb","parentId":"f8c61251","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:36:09.557Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the Phase 2 loop clearly. Lines 20-31 are the Phase 2 loop. I need to replace lines 20-31 with the DAgger version.\n\nBut the Phase 2 loop doesn't have markdown headers like `### Phase 2: ...`. It's just:\n```\nprint(f'Phase 2: Imitation learning ({IMITATION_EP} ep)')\n```\n\nSo my script was looking for `'### Phase 2'` but it was just `'Phase 2'`. Let me write a proper fix script that:\n1. Finds the Phase 2 loop (lines 20-31 in cell 10)\n\n\n2. Replaces it with the DAgger version\n\nThe Phase 2 loop spans from line 20 (the print statement) through line 31 (the closing of the for loop), and I need to substitute this entire section with the DAgger implementation.","thinkingSignature":"1fa30195acfbe1fde34ec292ca3696c044abddb078eb6d4c12f3b039bfc4797a"},{"type":"text","text":"Now I see — Phase 2 is plain `print` lines, not `### Phase 2` markdown. Lines 20-31 in cell 10. Let me write the fix:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4exi2ndenget_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\fix_phase2.py","content":"import json, sys\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    nb = json.load(f)\n\n# Cell 10 is the training cell\ncell10 = nb['cells'][10]\nlines = cell10['source']\n\n# Find the Phase 2 loop: starts at \"print(f'Phase 2:\" line, ends after its for loop\np2_start = None\np2_end = None\nfor i, line in enumerate(lines):\n    if \"print(f'Phase 2:\" in line:\n        p2_start = i\n    if p2_start is not None and \"print(f'Phase 2 done\" in line:\n        p2_end = i + 1  # include the print line\n        break\n\nprint(f\"Phase 2 loop found: lines {p2_start} to {p2_end}\")\nfor i in range(p2_start, p2_end):\n    sys.stdout.write(\"%3d: %s\\n\" % (i, lines[i].encode('ascii', 'replace').decode()))\n\n# New Phase 2 loop\nnew_phase2 = [\n    \"print(f'Phase 2: DAgger ({IMITATION_EP} ep)')\\n\",\n    \"t0 = time.time()\\n\",\n    \"dagger_buffer = DAggerReplayBuffer(max_size=5000)\\n\",\n    \"phase2_ep = 0\\n\",\n    \"collect_every = 3  # collect DAgger trajectory every N steps\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"for ep in range(IMITATION_EP):\\n\",\n    \"    phase2_ep += 1\\n\",\n    \"    beta = _beta_schedule(phase2_ep)\\n\",\n    \"    \\n\",\n    \"    # Every N steps: collect DAgger trajectory from current policy\\n\",\n    \"    if phase2_ep % collect_every == 0:\\n\",\n    \"        coll_ep = generate_episode(DEEPSEED + ep + 100000)\\n\",\n    \"        coll_stats = dagger_collection_episode(model, coll_ep, dagger_buffer, DEVICE)\\n\",\n    \"        if coll_stats is not None and phase2_ep % 200 == 0:\\n\",\n    \"            print(f'  coll {phase2_ep:5d}: blkd={coll_stats[\\\"blocked_frac\\\"]:.2f} '\\n\",\n    \"                  f'buf={coll_stats[\\\"buffer_size\\\"]} '\\n\",\n    \"                  f'wr={coll_stats[\\\"write_frac\\\"]:.2f} rd={coll_stats[\\\"read_frac\\\"]:.2f}')\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"    # Training step: mix DAgger buffer + fresh oracle episodes\\n\",\n    \"    stats = {}\\n\",\n    \"    dagger_train_step(trainer, dagger_buffer, beta, DEVICE, collect_stats=stats)\\n\",\n    \"    \\n\",\n    \"    if phase2_ep % 200 == 0 or phase2_ep == IMITATION_EP:\\n\",\n    \"        print(f'  p2 {phase2_ep:5d}: beta={beta:.2f} loss={stats.get(\\\"mixed_loss\\\",0):.4f} '\\n\",\n    \"              f'd_l={stats.get(\\\"dagger_loss\\\",0):.4f} o_l={stats.get(\\\"oracle_loss\\\",0):.4f} '\\n\",\n    \"              f'buf={stats.get(\\\"buffer_size\\\",0)} acc={stats.get(\\\"oracle_acc\\\",0):.3f}')\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"print(f'Phase 2 done in {time.time()-t0:.0f}s\\\\n')\\n\",\n]\n\n# Replace\nnew_lines = lines[:p2_start] + new_phase2 + lines[p2_end:]\nnb['cells'][10]['source'] = new_lines\nprint(f\"\\nReplaced Phase 2 loop with DAgger version\")\nprint(f\"New total lines in cell 10: {len(new_lines)}\")\n\n# Verify: check that the key DAgger references are present in cell 10\nsrc10 = ''.join(new_lines)\nchecks = [\n    ('dagger_collection_episode', 'dagger_collection_episode in cell 10'),\n    ('_beta_schedule', '_beta_schedule in cell 10'),\n    ('dagger_buffer', 'dagger_buffer in cell 10'),\n    ('dagger_train_step', 'dagger_train_step in cell 10'),\n    ('Phase 3', 'Phase 3 still present'),\n]\nfor kw, desc in checks:\n    print(f\"  {desc}: {kw in src10}\")\n\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    json.dump(nb, f, ensure_ascii=False)\n\nprint(\"\\nNotebook saved.\")\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":61800,"output":1318,"cacheRead":14175,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77293,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774359328720}}
