{"type":"message","id":"9d38c7a8","parentId":"afb9ec0d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:37:51.000Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_q1nfs3mub2cg_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== Cell 6 (49 lines) ===\r\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\r\nfrom typing import List\r\n\r\nN_GENUINE = 20; EPISODE_LENGTH = 190; QUERY_START = 150\r\nIGNORE_INDEX = -100\r\n\r\n@dataclass\r\nclass Episode:\r\n    input_ids: torch.Tensor\r\n    oracle_actions: List[str]\r\n    target_value_ids: torch.Tensor\r\n    genuine_keys: List[int] = None\r\n    genuine_values: List[int] = None\r\n\r\ndef generate_episode(seed=0):\r\n    rng = random.Random(seed)\r\n    gk = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(N_GENUINE)]\r\n    gv = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(N_GENUINE)]\r\n    fk = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(60)]\r\n    fv = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(60)]\r\n\r\n    inp, ora = [], []\r\n    # Encode: 100 steps (50 key+value pairs)\r\n    for i in range(100):\r\n        if i % 2 == 0:\r\n            inp.append(gk[i//2] if i//2 < N_GENUINE else fk[i//2])\r\n            ora.app\r\n...\r\n=== Cell 7 (73 lines) ===\r\n# ???????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????\r\n# DAgger training mixin: adds dagger_train_episode to SRMoETrainer\r\n#\r\n# Phase 2 now alternates between:\r\n#   1. DAgger collection: run current policy, populate replay buffer\r\n#   2. DAgger training: train on buffer samples + fresh oracle episodes\r\n#\r\n# beta schedule: start at 0.8 (mostly oracle), decay to 0.2 over DECAY_EPS\r\n# ???????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????\r\n\r\nDAggerBuffer = DAggerReplayBuffer(max_size=5000)\r\n\r\nDECAY_EPS = 500       # episodes over which beta decays from 0.8 to 0.2\r\nINIT_BETA = 0.8       # start: 80% oracle actions, 20% policy states\r\nFINAL_BETA = 0.2      # end: 20% oracle actions, 80% policy states\r\nDAGGER_COLLECT_EVERY = 3   # collect DAgger every N training steps\r\nDAGGE\r\n...\r\n=== Cell 8 (185 lines) ===\r\nimport wandb\r\n\r\nclass SRMoETrainer:\r\n    def __init__(self, model, lr=3e-3, lambda_route=1.0, lambda_div=0.1,\r\n                 lambda_margin=1.0, margin_target=0.5,\r\n                 route_class_weights=[1.0, 10.0, 15.0]):\r\n        self.model = model.to(DEVICE)\r\n        self.lr = lr; self.lambda_route = lambda_route\r\n        self.lambda_div = lambda_div; self.lambda_margin = lambda_margin\r\n        self.margin_target = margin_target\r\n        self.route_class_weights = route_class_weights\r\n        self.lambda_density = 0.3  # FIX #4: penalize route density below threshold\r\n        self.params = (list(model.routing.parameters())\r\n            + list(model.output_head.parameters())\r\n            + list(model.gru.parameters()))  # FIX #2: GRU in trainable params so hidden carries task signal\r\n        self.opt \r\n..."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":666,"aggregated":"=== Cell 6 (49 lines) ===\r\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\r\nfrom typing import List\r\n\r\nN_GENUINE = 20; EPISODE_LENGTH = 190; QUERY_START = 150\r\nIGNORE_INDEX = -100\r\n\r\n@dataclass\r\nclass Episode:\r\n    input_ids: torch.Tensor\r\n    oracle_actions: List[str]\r\n    target_value_ids: torch.Tensor\r\n    genuine_keys: List[int] = None\r\n    genuine_values: List[int] = None\r\n\r\ndef generate_episode(seed=0):\r\n    rng = random.Random(seed)\r\n    gk = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(N_GENUINE)]\r\n    gv = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(N_GENUINE)]\r\n    fk = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(60)]\r\n    fv = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(60)]\r\n\r\n    inp, ora = [], []\r\n    # Encode: 100 steps (50 key+value pairs)\r\n    for i in range(100):\r\n        if i % 2 == 0:\r\n            inp.append(gk[i//2] if i//2 < N_GENUINE else fk[i//2])\r\n            ora.app\r\n...\r\n=== Cell 7 (73 lines) ===\r\n# ???????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????\r\n# DAgger training mixin: adds dagger_train_episode to SRMoETrainer\r\n#\r\n# Phase 2 now alternates between:\r\n#   1. DAgger collection: run current policy, populate replay buffer\r\n#   2. DAgger training: train on buffer samples + fresh oracle episodes\r\n#\r\n# beta schedule: start at 0.8 (mostly oracle), decay to 0.2 over DECAY_EPS\r\n# ???????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????\r\n\r\nDAggerBuffer = DAggerReplayBuffer(max_size=5000)\r\n\r\nDECAY_EPS = 500       # episodes over which beta decays from 0.8 to 0.2\r\nINIT_BETA = 0.8       # start: 80% oracle actions, 20% policy states\r\nFINAL_BETA = 0.2      # end: 20% oracle actions, 80% policy states\r\nDAGGER_COLLECT_EVERY = 3   # collect DAgger every N training steps\r\nDAGGE\r\n...\r\n=== Cell 8 (185 lines) ===\r\nimport wandb\r\n\r\nclass SRMoETrainer:\r\n    def __init__(self, model, lr=3e-3, lambda_route=1.0, lambda_div=0.1,\r\n                 lambda_margin=1.0, margin_target=0.5,\r\n                 route_class_weights=[1.0, 10.0, 15.0]):\r\n        self.model = model.to(DEVICE)\r\n        self.lr = lr; self.lambda_route = lambda_route\r\n        self.lambda_div = lambda_div; self.lambda_margin = lambda_margin\r\n        self.margin_target = margin_target\r\n        self.route_class_weights = route_class_weights\r\n        self.lambda_density = 0.3  # FIX #4: penalize route density below threshold\r\n        self.params = (list(model.routing.parameters())\r\n            + list(model.output_head.parameters())\r\n            + list(model.gru.parameters()))  # FIX #2: GRU in trainable params so hidden carries task signal\r\n        self.opt \r\n...","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774359470930}}
{"type":"message","id":"996364b0","parentId":"9d38c7a8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:38:05.065Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the structure:\n- Cell 6: Episode generation\n- Cell 7: DAgger trainer patch (dagger_train_step, _beta_schedule, DAggerBuffer init) ← this is the patch we inserted\n- Cell 8: SRMoETrainer (the original trainer class)\n\nThe cells are in the wrong order! The DAgger patch (cell 7) runs BEFORE the SRMoETrainer (cell 8). But `dagger_train_step` references `trainer` (an instance of SRMoETrainer), so it needs to run AFTER SRMoETrainer is defined. Also, `dagger_train_step` uses `generate_episode` which is in cell 6.\n\n\nThe correct order should be: SRMoETrainer (cell 8) first, then the DAgger patch (cell 7) after it since the patch depends on both the trainer class and the episode generation function. I need to swap these two cells.","thinkingSignature":"35443bf2d1876bdfc467eb2634b9047e4a7ff1a6a79b64f167794850da5efc9f"},{"type":"text","text":"Wrong order — DAgger patch (cell 7) runs *before* `SRMoETrainer` is defined (cell 8). Need to swap them:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yu3ar83hfk6p_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\swap_cells.py","content":"import json\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    nb = json.load(f)\n\ncells = nb['cells']\n\n# Swap cell 7 (dagger patch) and cell 8 (SRMoETrainer)\n# After swap: SRMoETrainer is defined first, then DAgger patch uses it\ncells[7], cells[8] = cells[8], cells[7]\n\nprint(\"Swapped cells 7 and 8\")\nprint(\"Cell 7 now starts with:\", ''.join(cells[7]['source'])[:60].encode('ascii','replace').decode())\nprint(\"Cell 8 now starts with:\", ''.join(cells[8]['source'])[:60].encode('ascii','replace').decode())\n\n# Verify the new order\nsrc7 = ''.join(cells[7]['source'])\nsrc8 = ''.join(cells[8]['source'])\nprint(\"\\nCell 7 has SRMoETrainer:\", 'class SRM