{"type":"message","id":"00fa329c","parentId":"7a1f7715","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:55:35.979Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that `dagger_train_step` is defined in cell 8 (the DAgger trainer patch). But earlier, when we swapped cells, cell 8 has `dagger_train_step` but cell 7 has `SRMoETrainer`. The `dagger_train_step` is a standalone function that takes `trainer` as an argument.\n\nThe key issue: when `dagger_train_step` runs `L_dagger.backward()`, the gradients should flow into `trainer.params` (which includes routing parameters). But `trainer.model` might still be in `eval()` mode from `dagger_collection_episode`.\n\nLet me check: `dagger_collection_episode` starts with `m = model.eval()`. \n\nSo the model stays in eval mode when `dagger_train_step` runs. That might be the problem. I need to switch the model back to training mode at the start of `dagger_train_step` to ensure gradients propagate correctly, and I should verify that `dagger_loss_from_buffer` is properly passing gradients through to the routing parameters.","thinkingSignature":"d8e1a6bc911d612a3982bcedf20a60bd941eedbc9da133aef0e9a1b0232d90fa"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b7n5oyxkguf6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\nimport json\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: nb = json.load(f)\nsrc = ''.join(nb['cells'][8]['source'])\nlines = src.split(chr(10))\nfor i, l in enumerate(lines):\n    print('%3d: %s' % (i+1, repr(l)[:100]))\n\" 2>&1 | head -70"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":95259,"output":340,"cacheRead":14175,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109774,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774364126246}}
