{"type":"message","id":"6ef71f15","parentId":"2d6b2417","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:34:02.642Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_vmmlc35aa7sc_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"dagger_train_step starts at line 25\r\n  25: def dagger_train_step(trainer, dagger_buffer, beta, device, collect_stats=None):\r\n  26:     \"\"\"\r\n  27:     One DAgger training step:\r\n  28:       - Sample DAGGER_BATCH_SIZE transitions from buffer, compute dagger loss\r\n  29:       - Generate ORACLE_EPISODES_PER_STEP fresh oracle episodes, compute oracle loss\r\n  30:       - Mix: dagger_loss*(1-beta) + oracle_loss*beta, single backward pass\r\n  31: \r\n  32:     CRITICAL: model must be in train() mode so autograd works.\r\n  33:     dagger_collection_episode sets model to eval() ? switch back here.\r\n  34:     Also: we DON'T call trainer.train_episode (it does its own backward internally).\r\n  35:     Instead run the forward pass manually and accumulate a single L_oracle tensor.\r\n  36:     \"\"\"\r\n  37:     # Force train mode ? dagger_collection_episode leaves model in eval() mode\r\n  38:     trainer.model.train()\r\n  39: \r\n  40:     # DAgger loss from buffer: forward pass through router with gradient\r\n  41:     L_dagger, d_info = dagger_loss_from_buffer(\r\n  42:         trainer.model, dagger_buffer, DAGGER_BATCH_SIZE, device\r\n  43:     )\r\n  44: \r\n  45:     # Oracle loss: run forward manually (NOT via train_episode ? it calls backward)\r\n  46:     L_oracle_total = torch.tensor(0.0, device=device)\r\n  47:     oracle_acc = 0.0\r\n  48:     for _ in range(ORACLE_EPISODES_PER_STEP):\r\n  49:         ep = generate_episode(int(random.random() * 1e6))\r\n  50:         ep_stats = _run_oracle_episode(trainer.model, ep, device)\r\n  51:         L_oracle_total = L_oracle_total + torch.tensor(ep_stats['loss'], device=device)\r\n  52:         oracle_acc = ep_stats.get('accuracy', 0.0)\r\n  53:     L_oracle = L_oracle_total / ORACLE_EPISODES_PER_STEP\r\n  54: \r\n  55:     # Mix losses and single backward pass\r\n  56:     L_mixed = (1 - beta) * L_dagger + beta * L_oracle\r\n  57: \r\n  58:     trainer.opt.zero_grad()\r\n  59:     L_mixed.backward()\r\n  60:     torch.nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(trainer.params, 1.0)\r\n  61:     trainer.opt.step()\r\n  62: \r\n  63:     if collect_stats is not None:\r\n  64:         collect_stats['dagger_loss'] = L_dagger.item()\r\n  65:         collect_stats['oracle_loss'] = L_oracle.item()\r\n  66:         collect_stats['mixed_loss'] = L_mixed.item()\r\n  67:         collect_stats['beta'] = beta\r\n  68:         collect_stats['buffer_size'] = len(dagger_buffer)\r\n  69:         collect_stats['dagger_samples'] = d_info.get('dagger_n_samples', 0)\r\n  70:         collect_stats['oracle_acc'] = oracle_acc\r\n  71: \r\n  72: \r\n  73: def _run_oracle_episode(model, episode, device):\r\n  74:     \"\"\""}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1116,"aggregated":"dagger_train_step starts at line 25\r\n  25: def dagger_train_step(trainer, dagger_buffer, beta, device, collect_stats=None):\r\n  26:     \"\"\"\r\n  27:     One DAgger training step:\r\n  28:       - Sample DAGGER_BATCH_SIZE transitions from buffer, compute dagger loss\r\n  29:       - Generate ORACLE_EPISODES_PER_STEP fresh oracle episodes, compute oracle loss\r\n  30:       - Mix: dagger_loss*(1-beta) + oracle_loss*beta, single backward pass\r\n  31: \r\n  32:     CRITICAL: model must be in train() mode so autograd works.\r\n  33:     dagger_collection_episode sets model to eval() ? switch back here.\r\n  34:     Also: we DON'T call trainer.train_episode (it does its own backward internally).\r\n  35:     Instead run the forward pass manually and accumulate a single L_oracle tensor.\r\n  36:     \"\"\"\r\n  37:     # Force train mode ? dagger_collection_episode leaves model in eval() mode\r\n  38:     trainer.model.train()\r\n  39: \r\n  40:     # DAgger loss from buffer: forward pass through router with gradient\r\n  41:     L_dagger, d_info = dagger_loss_from_buffer(\r\n  42:         trainer.model, dagger_buffer, DAGGER_BATCH_SIZE, device\r\n  43:     )\r\n  44: \r\n  45:     # Oracle loss: run forward manually (NOT via train_episode ? it calls backward)\r\n  46:     L_oracle_total = torch.tensor(0.0, device=device)\r\n  47:     oracle_acc = 0.0\r\n  48:     for _ in range(ORACLE_EPISODES_PER_STEP):\r\n  49:         ep = generate_episode(int(random.random() * 1e6))\r\n  50:         ep_stats = _run_oracle_episode(trainer.model, ep, device)\r\n  51:         L_oracle_total = L_oracle_total + torch.tensor(ep_stats['loss'], device=device)\r\n  52:         oracle_acc = ep_stats.get('accuracy', 0.0)\r\n  53:     L_oracle = L_oracle_total / ORACLE_EPISODES_PER_STEP\r\n  54: \r\n  55:     # Mix losses and single backward pass\r\n  56:     L_mixed = (1 - beta) * L_dagger + beta * L_oracle\r\n  57: \r\n  58:     trainer.opt.zero_grad()\r\n  59:     L_mixed.backward()\r\n  60:     torch.nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(trainer.params, 1.0)\r\n  61:     trainer.opt.step()\r\n  62: \r\n  63:     if collect_stats is not None:\r\n  64:         collect_stats['dagger_loss'] = L_dagger.item()\r\n  65:         collect_stats['oracle_loss'] = L_oracle.item()\r\n  66:         collect_stats['mixed_loss'] = L_mixed.item()\r\n  67:         collect_stats['beta'] = beta\r\n  68:         collect_stats['buffer_size'] = len(dagger_buffer)\r\n  69:         collect_stats['dagger_samples'] = d_info.get('dagger_n_samples', 0)\r\n  70:         collect_stats['oracle_acc'] = oracle_acc\r\n  71: \r\n  72: \r\n  73: def _run_oracle_episode(model, episode, device):\r\n  74:     \"\"\"","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774366442545}}
{"type":"message","id":"96567cc6","parentId":"6ef71f15","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:34:22.918Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The code in the notebook looks correct. The problem must be in `_run_oracle_episode`. Line 51 creates a new tensor from `ep_stats['loss']` — but `ep_stats['loss']` is a Python float (`.item()` was called somewhere). Wait no, `_run_oracle_episode` returns a dict with `loss.item()` which is a float. So `torch.tensor(ep_stats['loss'], device=device)` creates a NEW tensor without `requires_grad=True`.\n\nBUT — `_run_oracle_episode` computes `loss` as `L_answer + L_route + L_margin + L_div`, all of which are tensors with gradients. So `loss` is a tensor with gradients. \n\nWhen we do `{'loss': loss.item()}`, we're extracting a float from that tensor. So the fix is to use the tensor directly instead of converting it to a float and back — keep `loss` as the actual tensor, not `.item()`.\n\nIn `_run_oracle_episode`, I'm returning `loss.item()` in the dict, but then in `dagger_train_step` I'm wrapping it back in `torch.tensor(ep_stats['loss'], device=device)`, which creates a new tensor without gradient history. I need to return the tensor itself and accumulate it directly.\n\nLooking at the error traceback showing line 60 as the failing line, I'm wondering if there's a kernel caching issue where the old broken version of the function is still loaded in memory, not the updated version from the notebook. That would explain why the fix isn't taking effect even though the code looks correct. The real problem is that wrapping `loss.item()` in `torch.tensor()` strips the gradient history, so when I compute `L_mixed = (1-beta) * L_dagger + beta * L_oracle`, if either component lacks `requires_grad=True`, the whole thing fails. The fix is to have `_run_oracle_episode` return the loss tensor directly instead of converting it to a float first.","thinkingSignature":"dbed177493f2d168e042cf96772951190332cee2c9293ba93aa63ba587a107cb"},{"type":"text","text":"Found it. `_run_oracle_episode` returns `loss.item()` (a Python float), then `dagger_train_step` wraps it back in `torch.tensor(...)` which creates a new tensor **without `requires_grad=True`**. When one operand is non-grad, the sum is non-grad.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_w704l8zxgzmj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\nimport json\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: nb = json.load(f)\nsrc = ''.join(nb['cells'][8]['source'])\n# Fix: return loss TENSOR from _run_oracle_episode, not loss.item()\nold = \\\"'loss': loss.item(), 'answer_loss': L_answer.item(),\\\"\nnew = \\\"'loss': loss, 'answer_loss': L_answer.item(),\\\"\nprint('Has old return pattern:', old in src)\nnew_src = src.replace(old, new, 1)\nprint('Old == new?', old == new)\nnb['cells'][8]['source'] = [new_src]\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(nb, f, ensure_ascii=False)\nprint('Fixed: loss is now tensor, not .item()')\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":104441,"output":709,"cacheRead":14175,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":119325,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774366442648}}
