{"type":"message","id":"f66fd726","parentId":"f6adf7fa","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:37:59.477Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, there's an issue. The `else:` at line 21 should introduce a new block before `print(f'Phase 1:...')`. But the way it looks, the `else:` and the `print(f'Phase 1:...')` are separate statements without proper indentation. The `else:` should be followed by a block that's indented more than the print statement.Let me check the full context more carefully. The `else:` block should be:\n```\nelse:\n    print(f'Phase 1: Supervised pre-training...')\n    t0 = time.time()\n    for ep in range(PRETRAIN_EP):\n        ...\n\n\n```\n\nI see the problem now — the `else:` on line 21 is dangling without proper indentation or an accompanying `if` statement. It needs to be indented to match the `if` block above it, and then all the subsequent Phase 1 code needs to be indented under it as the `else` body.\n\nFixing the indentation...\n\n```","thinkingSignature":"87554a5b21a47d2e1a8754c0dd66a02bda33a1487bd5f43cc2969d7a74fb8471"},{"type":"text","text":"There's an indentation issue — the `else:` at line 21 isn't properly indented under the `if SKIP_PHASE1` block. Let me fix that:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zlu1lswgjpj5_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\fix_indent.py","content":"import json\n\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    nb = json.load(f)\n\nsrc = ''.join(nb['cells'][10]['source'])\n\n# The if/else block was inserted without proper indentation\n# Current (broken):\n#   if SKIP_PHASE1 and os.path.exists(PHASE1_CKPT):\n#       ...load...\n#   else:                        <- needs to indent\n# print(f'Phase 1:...')         <- needs to indent under else\n\nold_block = \"\"\"# Load Phase 1 checkpoint and skip training if configured\nif SKIP_PHASE1 and os.path.exists(PHASE1_CKPT):\n    ckpt = torch.load(PHASE1_CKPT, map_location=DEVICE)\n    model.load_state_dict(ckpt['model_state'])\n    trainer.opt.load_state_dict(ckpt['optimizer_state'])\n    if hasattr(model.routing, '_step'):\n        model.routing._step = ckpt.get('ep_count', PRETRAIN_EP)\n    print(f'Loaded Phase 1 checkpoint from {PHASE1_CKPT} - skipping Phase 1\\\\n')\nelse:\nprint(f'Phase 1: Supervised pre-training ({PRETRAIN_EP} ep)')\"\"\"\n\nnew_block = \"\"\"# Load Phase 1 checkpoint and skip training if configured\nif SKIP_PHASE1 and os.path.exists(PHASE1_CKPT):\n    ckpt = torch.load(PHASE1_CKPT, map_location=DEVICE)\n    model.load_state_dict(ckpt['model_state'])\n    trainer.opt.load_state_dict(ckpt['optimizer_state'])\n    if hasattr(model.routing, '_step'):\n        model.routing._step = ckpt.get('ep_count', PRETRAIN_EP)\n    print(f'Loaded Phase 1 checkpoint from {PHASE1_CKPT} - skipping Phase 1\\\\n')\nelse:\n    print(f'Phase 1: Supervised pre-training ({PRETRAIN_EP} ep)')\n    t0 = time.time()\n    for ep in range(PRETRAIN_EP):\n        stats = trainer.train_episode(generate_episode(DEEPSEED + ep), use_oracle_routing=True)\n        if ep % 200 == 0 or ep == PRETRAIN_EP - 1:\n            print(f'  ep {ep:5d}: loss={stats[\"loss\"]:.4f}  acc={stats[\"accuracy\"]:.3f}  '\n                  f'route_ce={stats[\"route_loss\"]:.4f}  div={stats[\"div_loss\"]:.4f}  '\n                  f'wr={stats[\"write_frac\"]:.2f}  rd={stats[\"read_frac\"]:.2f}  '\n                  f'skip={stats[\"skip_frac\"]:.2f}  occ={stats[\"avg_occupancy\"]:.1f}')\n    print(f'  Phase 1 done in {time.time()-t0:.0f}s\\\\n')\n    \n    # Save Phase 1 checkpoint\n    torch.save({\n        'model_state': model.state_dict(),\n        'optimizer_state': trainer.opt.state_dict(),\n        'tau': model.routing.tau if hasattr(model.routing, 'tau') else None,\n        'ep_count': PRETRAIN_EP,\n    }, PHASE1_CKPT)\n    print(f'Phase 1 checkpoint saved to {PHASE1_CKPT}\\\\n')\"\"\"\n\nif old_block in src:\n    new_src = src.replace(old_block, new_block)\n    nb['cells'][10]['source'] = [new_src]\n    with open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n        json.dump(nb, f, ensure_ascii=False)\n    print(\"Fixed indentation — else block now properly indented\")\nelse:\n    print(\"WARNING: exact text match not found — showing what we have:\")\n    for i, l in enumerate(src.split('\\n')[12:30]):\n        print('%3d: %s' % (i+12, repr(l)))\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":100540,"output":1170,"cacheRead":14175,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":115885,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774366652423}}
