{"type":"message","id":"5d346b44","parentId":"fd1990c5","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:13:46.110Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Paperspace Gradient free tier probably doesn't allow persistent file storage. The checkpoint would need to be saved somewhere accessible or not at all.\n\nOptions:\n1. Save to a Google Drive or cloud location\n2. Use wandb to save the checkpoint (Weights & Biases has artifact storage)\n3. Disable the checkpoint entirely and just run fresh each time\n4. Save to a mounted cloud storage location\n\nActually, for Paperspace Gradient, the `/workspace` directory is the mounted cloud storage. But maybe it's read-only or doesn't exist by default on free tier.\n\nLet me think about what makes sense:\n- For a free tier notebook, persistent storage might be limited\n- Weights & Biases artifact storage would work — we already have wandb integrated\n- We could save the checkpoint as a wandb artifact instead of a file\n\n\n- The simplest approach is probably just disabling the checkpoint since we're still debugging Phase 2 anyway, so re-running Phase 1 each time isn't too costly\n\nLet me check what directory actually exists on Paperspace Gradient.","thinkingSignature":"867f772bca1eee9f5d8cef9189fbae42a2633603528cfafff44857c7c25731de"},{"type":"text","text":"Paperspace free tier likely doesn't have persistent `/workspace` storage. Simplest fix — just disable the checkpoint save since it's still in active debugging anyway:\n\n```\nPHASE1_CKPT = None  # disable checkpointing during development\n```\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m2zvezy28kr4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\nimport json\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: nb = json.load(f)\nsrc = nb['cells'][10]['source'][0]\nold = \\\"PHASE1_CKPT = '/workspace/phase1_checkpoint.pt'\\\"\nnew = \\\"PHASE1_CKPT = None  # disable during development (no persistent storage on free tier)\\\"\n