{"type":"message","id":"18d208ff","parentId":"7f387d6e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:17:47.454Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the structure looks right:\n- Cell 10 is the new checkpoint cell\n- Cell 11 is the training cell (which now has Phase 2 DAgger)\n\nThe checkpoint cell has the right content. Now I need to verify that the training cell (cell 11) is the original training cell with Phase 1/2/3 and hasn't been corrupted. Let me also check that the checkpoint cell's SKIP_PHASE1 logic properly controls whether Phase 1 runs.\n\nActually, there's one issue: the new checkpoint cell I created has Phase 1 inline, but the training cell (old cell 10) also has Phase 1. This means Phase 1 would be defined in BOTH cells and would run TWICE — once in the checkpoint cell and once in the training cell.\n\n\nI see the problem now — I'm duplicating the Phase 1 code instead of replacing it. The checkpoint cell has the Phase 1 loop inline, but the original training cell also still contains its Phase 1 loop, so both would execute. I need to either have the checkpoint cell handle all Phase 1 logic and remove it from the training cell, or restructure so the training cell only handles Phases 2 and 3. Phase 1 ends and the checkpoint is saved, then Phase 2 kicks in through the training cell. This creates a redundancy issue, so I need to remove Phase 1 from the training cell since the checkpoint cell already handles it.","thinkingSignature":"b2c321deb6b6a9c6aae6bb8a6426cff1c1c752d73fba6b47c4ab408266fdc6c4"},{"type":"text","text":"There's duplication — Phase 1 runs in both cells. I need to remove Phase 1 from the training cell since the checkpoint cell now owns it:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gs5o4tq4j76a_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\fix_dup.py","content":"import json, sys\n\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'r', encoding='utf-8', errors='replace') as f:\n    nb = json.load(f)\n\n# Cell 11 is the training cell (old cell 10)\n# It still has Phase 1 loop. We need to remove it and start from Phase 2.\ncell11 = nb['cells'][11]\nsrc = ''.join(cell11['source'])\nlines = cell11['source']\n\n# Find Phase 2 start in the training cell\np2_start = None\nfor i, line in enumerate(lines):\n    if \"Phase 2\" in line and \"DAgger\" in line:\n        p2_start = i\n        break\n\nprint(\"Cell 11 total lines:\", len(lines))\nprint(\"Phase 2 starts at line:\", p2_start)\nif p2_start:\n    for i in range(max(0, p2_start-2), min(p2_start+3, len(lines))):\n        sys.stdout.write(\"%3d: %s\\n\" % (i, lines[i].encode('ascii','replace').decode()))\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":107134,"output":617,"cacheRead":14175,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":121926,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774369052085}}
