{"type":"message","id":"d8aadb32","parentId":"6e0fe593","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:18:19.020Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the structure. Cell 11 has lines 0-7 (constants and comments) and lines 9-18 (Phase 1 loop), and then Phase 2 at line 20.\n\nThe checkpoint cell (cell 10) already has Phase 1 inline with SKIP_PHASE1 control. So I need to:\n1. Keep lines 0-7 in cell 11 (constants are needed for Phase 2 and Phase 3)\n2. Remove lines 9-18 (Phase 1) from cell 11\n3. Keep Phase 2 and Phase 3\n\nBut wait - the constants PRETRAIN_EP, IMITATION_EP, HARDEN_EP are already defined in the checkpoint cell (cell 10) via SKIP_PHASE1. \n\nSo they're duplicated across cells, but that's actually fine since they'll just get overwritten. What really matters is that Phase 2 and Phase 3 reference these constants, so I need to preserve lines 0-7 in cell 11 to keep Phase 2 working. My plan is to remove Phase 1 from cell 11 (lines 9-18, which includes the loop, logging, and timing) and keep everything else intact. Let me check what's in cell 10 first to confirm this approach works.","thinkingSignature":"7c3d21232a34a98d62e51b44712f99c69fda33608eceb7bdf569d1eeb619ee2b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mq9ujc3851l3_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\fix_dup.py","content":"import json\n\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'r', encoding='utf-8', errors='replace') as f:\n    nb = json.load(f)\n\n# Remove Phase 1 (lines 9-18) from training cell (cell 11), keep Phase 2 and 3\nlines = nb['cells'][11]['source']\n\n# Keep lines 0-8 (up to and including HARDEN_EP), remove Phase 1 loop (9-18), keep 19+\nnew_lines = lines[:9] + lines[19:]  # skip Phase 1 loop entirely\n\nnb['cells'][11]['source'] = new_lines\nprint(\"Training cell now has %d lines (was %d)\" % (len(new_lines), len(lines)))\nprint(\"Phase 1 removed from training cell\")\nprint(\"Phase 2 and Phase 3 preserve