{"type":"message","id":"812082f7","parentId":"f609a169","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:27:08.773Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The backup already has the gradient fixes:\n1. `L_oracle_total = L_oracle_total + ep_stats['loss']` (not wrapped in torch.tensor)\n2. `'loss': loss` (returns tensor, not .item())\n3. `model.train()` is present\n\nAnd the `_run_oracle_episode` function is there too. The backup is good to use.\n\nNow I need to:\n1. Fix `_O2I` in cell 3's `dagger_collection_episode` — it uses `_O2I` but the variable is `ORACLE_TO_ACTION_IDX` in cell 4\n2. Add `PRETRAIN_EP` etc. \n\nI'll insert a new checkpoint cell after the model instantiation that defines these constants, adds the `_O2I` alias in cell 3, and wraps the Phase 1 loop in a checkpoint condition to handle the missing constants.","thinkingSignature":"ef24ef6023c0c6013154d535f57eec165fd97e7b99834724305636c565561ff6"},{"type":"text","text":"Good — backup has the gradient fixes. Now let me write the fix properly:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_e6zpqpixkv54_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\fix_all.py","content":"import json, sys\n\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'r', encoding='utf-8', errors='replace') as f:\n    nb = json.load(f)\n\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# FIX 1: Cell 3 — dagger_collection_episode uses _O2I but it's ORACLE_TO_ACTION_IDX\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\ncell3_src = ''.join(nb['cells'][3]['source'])\n\n# Add _O2I alias right after the imports section\n# Find the line with DAggerReplayBuffer class and insert before it\nif '_O2I = ORACLE_TO_ACTION_IDX' not in cell3_src:\n    # Find a good insertion point — after the docstring/comment block, before class\n    lines = cell3_src.split('\\n')\n    insert_idx = 0\n    for i, line in enumerate(lines):\n        if 'class DAggerReplayBuffer' in line:\n            insert_idx = i\n            break\n    # Insert alias before class\n    lines.insert(insert_idx, '_O2I = ORACLE_TO_ACTION_IDX  # alias for brevity\\n')\n    new_cell3_src = '\\n'.join(lines)\n    nb['cells'][3]['source'] = [new_cell3_src]\n    print(\"Fixed: added _O2I alias to cell 3\")\nelse:\n    print(\"Cell 3 already has _O2I\")\n\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# FIX 2: Cell 10 — add PRETRAIN_EP etc. so they're in scope\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\ncell10_src = ''.join(nb['cells'][10]['source'])\n\n# Add constants right at the top of cell 10\nconsts = \"\"\"# Training constants (needed in scope for checkpoint cell)\nPRETRAIN_EP = 2000\nIMITATION_EP = 5000\nHARDEN_EP = 2000\nDEEPSEED = 42\n\n\"\"\"\n\nif 'PRETRAIN_EP = 2000' not in cell10_src:\n    lines = nb['cells'][10]['source']\n    # Insert at very start\n    lines = [consts] + lines\n    nb['cells'][10]['source'] = lines\n    print(\"Fixed: added PRETRAIN_EP/IMITATION_EP/HARDEN_EP/DEEPSEED to cell 10\")\nelse:\n    print(\"Cell 10 already has constants\")\n\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# FIX 3: Disable the torch.save checkpoint (no persistent storage on free tier)\n# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\ncell10_src = ''.join(nb['cells'][10]['source'])\nif 'torch.save({' in cell10_src:\n    # Find the torch.save block and comment it out\n    old_save = \"torch.save({\"\n    new_save = \"# torch.save disabled (no persistent storage on free tier)\\n# torch.save({\"\n    new_cell10_src = cell10_src.replace(old_save, new_save, 1)\n    # Also comment out the if PHASE1_CKPT line\n    new_cell10_src = new_cell10_src.replace(\n        \"if PHASE1_CKPT is not None:\",\n        \"if False:  # disabled\"\n    )\n    nb['cells'][10]['source'] = [new_cell10_src]\n    print(\"Fixed: disable